&gt; like a thresher?&quot;
&gt;
&gt; What Wheelie feared..  What if the Dinobots truly had gone to hate all, even
&gt; their allies, for how they had been treated?  What would they do then?  He
&gt; could not fight his old friends.  He wasn&#39;t sure how he would respond then.
&gt; Or what Rodimus would do either.

&lt;NEW&gt;

RODIMUS looked at WHEELIE, his optics bright with fear, concern and a
host of other less clear yet powerful emotions. &quot;I don&#39;t know if the
Dinobots can be saved.&quot; He said finally. &quot;It could be they have chosen
to become what they are or it could be they have been forced.&quot; There
was a frown, &quot;I would go and offer than a choice, but now I must leave
that up to you.&quot;

&gt; &lt;OLD&gt;
&gt;
&gt; He nodded quietly, &quot;I will go, and here you stay.  Be safe, and when ready
&gt; go away.  Find the rest, and let them know.  For until then, take care we
&gt; both shall go.&quot;

&lt;NEW&gt;

There was a quiet smile, &quot;Go my friend and take care. I shall follow
as soon as I am able.&quot; He chuckled, &quot;When this is over, I owe you a
drink at Maccadam&#39;s.&quot;

